-- Hungary’s National Resources Minister Rethelyi Quits, MTI Says
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-05-03T11:19:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/hungary-s-national-resources-minister-rethelyi-quits-mti-says.html
Hungarian National Resources Minister
Miklos Rethelyi has quit, state-run news service  MTI  reported,
citing  Peter Szijjarto , Prime Minister Viktor Orban’s spokesman.  Orban asked Zoltan Balog, a state secretary, to succeed
Rethelyi as the minister in charge of health care, education,
social services and culture, MTI said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  